==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] ''dexter'' "right hand", deriving from ancient Greek ''dexiteros'', a poetic form of  ''dexios'' "right hand, skilful, fortunate".

===Adjective===
'''dexter'''

First and second conjugation

# [[right]] (''as opposed to left'')
#{{heraldry}}: The right side of a shield from the wearer's standpoint, and the left side to the viewer.

